```python def UpdateControllerWithNewSensorLinkPose( self, sensorSelectionInfo, # type: sensorSelectionInfoType sensorLinkInWorldMatrix, # type: numpy.ndarray webstackclient, # type: Any planningclient, # type: Any ): # type: (...) -> bool """Updates the controller scene with a new sensor link transform for sensorSelectionInfo, without disturbing the other sensors
Args: sensorLinkInWorldMatrix (ndarray): 4x4 matrix of the sensor link transform in the world
Returns: isUpdated (bool): True if updated """ sensorLinkInfo = GetSensorLinkPosesFromScene(self._scenepk, [sensorSelectionInfo], webstackclient, planningclient)[0] sensorLinkInWorldPose = basicmath.ConvertPoseFromMatrix(sensorLinkInWorldMatrix)
# camera is stationary in the scene if sensorLinkInfo['isBaseLink']: # should change the object transform instead since it is the base link! objectPk = sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyObjectPk'] if 'connectedBodyObjectPk' in sensorLinkInfo else sensorLinkInfo['objectPk']
# If there are other links attached to this instobject, then those sensors need to have their links moved to preserve their transform objectLinks = webstackclient.GetObjectLinks(objectPk)['links']
# for all the links not the base, should update the transform accordingly baseLinkPose = objectLinks[0]['quaternion'] + objectLinks[0]['translate'] invBaseLinkPose = basicmath.InvertPose(baseLinkPose) for ilink, objectLink in enumerate(objectLinks): if ilink > 0: linkPose = objectLink['quaternion'] + objectLink['translate'] relativeLinkPose = basicmath.MultiplyPose(invBaseLinkPose, linkPose).tolist() else: relativeLinkPose = [1,0,0,0,0,0,0] webstackclient.SetObjectLink(objectPk, objectLink['pk'], linkdata={'quaternion': relativeLinkPose[:4], 'translate': relativeLinkPose[4:]})
# now change the inst object transform if sensorLinkInfo.get('connectedBodyPk'): # move the connected body instead sensorLinkInFramePose = basicmath.MultiplyPose(basicmath.InvertPose(sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyFramePose']), sensorLinkInWorldPose) webstackclient.SetRobotConnectedBody(sensorLinkInfo['objectPk'], sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyPk'], connectedBodyData={'quaternion':sensorLinkInFramePose[:4].tolist(), 'translate':sensorLinkInFramePose[4:].tolist()}) else: webstackclient.SetSceneInstObject(self._scenepk, sensorLinkInfo['instObjectPk'], instobjectdata={'quaternion': sensorLinkInWorldPose[:4].tolist(), 'translate': sensorLinkInWorldPose[4:].tolist()}) else: parentLinkInfo = planningclient.GetLinkParentInfo(sensorSelectionInfo['sensorName'], sensorSelectionInfo['sensorLinkName']) parentLinkPose = parentLinkInfo['quaternion'] + parentLinkInfo['translation'] relativeLinkPoseInParentLink = basicmath.MultiplyPose(basicmath.InvertPose(parentLinkPose), sensorLinkInWorldPose) if sensorLinkInfo.get('connectedBodyObjectPk'): # on a connected body, so need the correct transform with respect to the connected body origin webstackclient.SetObjectLink(sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyObjectPk'], sensorLinkInfo['linkPk'], linkdata={'quaternion': relativeLinkPoseInParentLink[:4].tolist(), 'translate': relativeLinkPoseInParentLink[4:].tolist()}) else: webstackclient.SetObjectLink(sensorLinkInfo['objectPk'], sensorLinkInfo['linkPk'], linkdata={'quaternion': relativeLinkPoseInParentLink[:4].tolist(), 'translate': relativeLinkPoseInParentLink[4:].tolist()}) return True
```

```python def UpdateControllerWithCalibrationResult( self, calibrationProfileId, # type: str updateType, # type: str webstackclient, # type: Any planningclient, # type: Any sensorbridgeclient, # type: Any ): # type: (...) -> bool """Upload the calibration result of all calibrated attached sensor(s) in sensorName to mujin controller.
If any of the sensor links are also the base link of the object, then should change the object transform to match the sensor link transform! Because of this dependency order, have to process base sensor links first before processing any of the others.
Returns: isUpdated (bool): True if updated """ if self._hasResultsCalibrationProfileId != calibrationProfileId: log.warn(u'Cannot apply result of calibrationProfileId "%s" since do not have it loaded.', calibrationProfileId) return False
for isProcessBaseLink in [True, False]: # process base first # get every time since inst objects and/or connected bodies could have moved during after the base link processing sensorLinkInfos = GetSensorLinkPosesFromScene(self._scenepk, [calibrationresult['sensorSelectionInfo'] for calibrationresult in self._calibrationresults], webstackclient, planningclient) for iresult, calibrationresult in enumerate(self._calibrationresults): sensorLinkInfo = sensorLinkInfos[iresult] if sensorLinkInfo['isBaseLink'] != isProcessBaseLink: continue if updateType not in calibrationresult: log.warn('Could not find updateType=%r', updateType) continue calibrationResultUpdate = calibrationresult[updateType] log.info('Uploading the "%s" calibration result of sensorSelectionInfo=%r, imageType=%r to mujin controller, sensorLinkInfo=%r', updateType, calibrationresult['sensorSelectionInfo'], calibrationresult['imageType'], sensorLinkInfo)
if calibrationresult.get('sensorCalibrateFrameLinkName'): if 'sensorLinkInCalibrateFrameMatrix' in calibrationResultUpdate: # sensor is on the robot (eye-in-hand calibration) if sensorLinkInfo['isBaseLink']: if not sensorLinkInfo.get('connectedBodyPk'): raise CalibrationManagerError(_('sensorLink "%s" is a base link of its object, but it also has sensorCalibrateFrameLinkName "%s", which is not possible to calibrate.')%(calibrationresult['sensorSelectionInfo']['sensorLinkName'], calibrationresult['sensorCalibrateFrameLinkName']))
# check that the attaching link of the connected body is sensorCalibrateFrameLinkName connectedBodyData = webstackclient.GetRobotConnectedBody(sensorLinkInfo['objectPk'], sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyPk']) robotData = webstackclient.GetRobot(sensorLinkInfo['objectPk'])
# Getting frame origin name frameOriginName = None for link in robotData['links']: if link['pk'] == connectedBodyData['frame_origin']: frameOriginName = link['name'] break
if frameOriginName is None or frameOriginName != calibrationresult.get('sensorCalibrateFrameLinkName'): raise CalibrationManagerError(_('sensorLink "%s" is a base link of its object, but it also has sensorCalibrateFrameLinkName "%s" that does not match the frame_origin "%s" of the connectedBody "%s".')%(calibrationresult['sensorSelectionInfo']['sensorLinkName'], calibrationresult['sensorCalibrateFrameLinkName'], connectedBodyData['frame_origin'], sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyName']))
sensorLinkInCalibrateFramePose = basicmath.ConvertPoseFromMatrix(calibrationResultUpdate['sensorLinkInCalibrateFrameMatrix']).tolist() webstackclient.SetRobotConnectedBody(sensorLinkInfo['objectPk'], sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyPk'], connectedBodyData={'quaternion':sensorLinkInCalibrateFramePose[:4], 'translate':sensorLinkInCalibrateFramePose[4:]}) else: linkNamePrefix = u'' if sensorLinkInfo.get('connectedBodyName'): linkNamePrefix = sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyName'] + '_'
# have to find the transform of the calibrateFrame that the sensor link was calibrated against objectPk = sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyObjectPk'] if 'connectedBodyObjectPk' in sensorLinkInfo else sensorLinkInfo['objectPk'] objectLinks = webstackclient.GetObjectLinks(objectPk)['links'] sensorCalibrateFrameLink = None for objectLink in objectLinks: if linkNamePrefix + objectLink['name'] == calibrationresult['sensorCalibrateFrameLinkName']: sensorCalibrateFrameLink = objectLink break
if sensorCalibrateFrameLink is None: raise CalibrationManagerError(_('Could not find sensorCalibrateFrameLinkName "%s" that the sensorLink "%s" was calibrated against.')%(calibrationresult['sensorCalibrateFrameLinkName'], calibrationresult['sensorSelectionInfo']['sensorLinkName']))
#sensorCalibrateFrameLinkPose = sensorCalibrateFrameLink['quaternion'] + sensorCalibrateFrameLink['translate'] #sensorLinkInBodyMatrix = basicmath.MultiplyPose(sensorCalibrateFrameLinkPose, calibrationResultUpdate['sensorLinkInCalibrateFrameMatrix']) #sensorLinkInBodyPose = basicmath.ConvertPoseFromMatrix(sensorLinkInBodyMatrix).tolist() sensorLinkInCalibrateFramePose = basicmath.ConvertPoseFromMatrix(calibrationResultUpdate['sensorLinkInCalibrateFrameMatrix']) log.info(u'Updating sensor link transformation of sensorSelectionInfo=%s relative to calibrateFrameLink "%s"', calibrationresult['sensorSelectionInfo'], sensorLinkInCalibrateFramePose)
# SetObjectLink takes the relative transform with respect to the parent link. Because sensorCalibrateFrameLinkName is the parent of sensorLinkInfo['linkPk'], can just apply sensorLinkInCalibrateFramePose directly webstackclient.SetObjectLink(objectPk, sensorLinkInfo['linkPk'], linkdata={'quaternion': sensorLinkInCalibrateFramePose[:4].tolist(), 'translate': sensorLinkInCalibrateFramePose[4:].tolist()}) else: if 'sensorLinkMatrix' in calibrationResultUpdate: # camera is stationary in the scene if sensorLinkInfo['isBaseLink']: # should change the object transform instead since it is the base link! objectPk = sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyObjectPk'] if 'connectedBodyObjectPk' in sensorLinkInfo else sensorLinkInfo['objectPk']
# If there are other links attached to this instobject, then those sensors need to have their links moved to preserve their transform objectLinks = webstackclient.GetObjectLinks(objectPk)['links']
# for all the links not the base, should update the transform accordingly baseLinkPose = objectLinks[0]['quaternion'] + objectLinks[0]['translate'] # the base invBaseLinkPose = basicmath.InvertPose(baseLinkPose) for ilink, objectLink in enumerate(objectLinks): if ilink > 0: linkPose = objectLink['quaternion'] + objectLink['translate'] relativeLinkPose = basicmath.MultiplyPose(invBaseLinkPose, linkPose).tolist() else: relativeLinkPose = [1,0,0,0,0,0,0] # TODO replace with ModifyLink graphql command webstackclient.SetObjectLink(objectPk, objectLink['pk'], linkdata={'quaternion': relativeLinkPose[:4], 'translate': relativeLinkPose[4:]})
# now change the inst object transform sensorLinkInWorldPose = basicmath.ConvertPoseFromMatrix(calibrationResultUpdate['sensorLinkMatrix']) if sensorLinkInfo.get('connectedBodyPk'): # move the connected body instead log.info('connectedBodyFramePose=%r, sensorLinkInWorldPose=%r', sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyFramePose'], sensorLinkInWorldPose) sensorLinkInFramePose = basicmath.MultiplyPose(basicmath.InvertPose(sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyFramePose']), sensorLinkInWorldPose) webstackclient.SetRobotConnectedBody(sensorLinkInfo['objectPk'], sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyPk'], connectedBodyData={'quaternion':sensorLinkInFramePose[:4].tolist(), 'translate':sensorLinkInFramePose[4:].tolist()}) else: webstackclient.SetSceneInstObject(self._scenepk, sensorLinkInfo['instObjectPk'], instobjectdata={'quaternion': sensorLinkInWorldPose[:4].tolist(), 'translate': sensorLinkInWorldPose[4:].tolist()}) else: parentLinkInfo = planningclient.GetLinkParentInfo(calibrationresult['sensorSelectionInfo']['sensorName'], calibrationresult['sensorSelectionInfo']['sensorLinkName']) parentLinkPose = parentLinkInfo['quaternion'] + parentLinkInfo['translation'] relativeLinkPoseInParentLink = basicmath.MultiplyPose(basicmath.InvertPose(parentLinkPose), basicmath.ConvertPoseFromMatrix(calibrationResultUpdate['sensorLinkMatrix'])) if sensorLinkInfo.get('connectedBodyObjectPk'): # on a connected body, so need the correct transform with respect to the connected body origin webstackclient.SetObjectLink(sensorLinkInfo['connectedBodyObjectPk'], sensorLinkInfo['linkPk'], linkdata={'quaternion': relativeLinkPoseInParentLink[:4].tolist(), 'translate': relativeLinkPoseInParentLink[4:].tolist()}) else: webstackclient.SetObjectLink(sensorLinkInfo['objectPk'], sensorLinkInfo['linkPk'], linkdata={'quaternion': relativeLinkPoseInParentLink[:4].tolist(), 'translate': relativeLinkPoseInParentLink[4:].tolist()})
# pattern if 'calibrationBoardPath' in calibrationresult: if 'patternInLinkMatrix' in calibrationResultUpdate: patternInLinkPose = basicmath.ConvertPoseFromMatrix(calibrationResultUpdate['patternInLinkMatrix'])
calibrationBoardPathParts = ParseCalibrationBoardPath(calibrationresult['calibrationBoardPath'])
# although not sensor, can still reuse the function calibrationGeomInfo = GetSensorLinkPosesFromScene(self._scenepk, [{'sensorName':calibrationBoardPathParts[0], 'sensorLinkName':calibrationBoardPathParts[1]}], webstackclient, planningclient)[0] objectPk = calibrationGeomInfo['connectedBodyObjectPk'] if 'connectedBodyObjectPk' in calibrationGeomInfo else calibrationGeomInfo['objectPk']
# find the geometry pk of the pattern geometry objectGeometries = webstackclient.GetObjectGeometries(objectPk) for geometry in objectGeometries: if geometry['linkpk'] == calibrationGeomInfo['linkPk'] and geometry['name'] == calibrationBoardPathParts[2]: webstackclient.SetObjectGeometry(objectPk, geometry['pk'], {'quaternion':patternInLinkPose[:4].tolist(), 'translate':patternInLinkPose[4:].tolist()}) log.info(u'Setting transform of geom "%s" relative to link to pose=%r', calibrationresult['calibrationBoardPath'], patternInLinkPose)
if 'KK' in calibrationResultUpdate: log.info(u'Updating intrinsics for sensorSelectionInfo %s', calibrationresult['sensorSelectionInfo'])
# should update the attached sensor based on the relative transform from 'sensorLinkMatrix' attachedSensorTransform = None if 'sensorInWorldMatrix' in calibrationResultUpdate: relativeMatrix = dot(linalg.inv(calibrationResultUpdate['sensorLinkMatrix']), calibrationResultUpdate['sensorInWorldMatrix']) attachedSensorTransform = basicmath.ConvertPoseFromMatrix(relativeMatrix).tolist()
self._SetIntrinsicsToSensorBridge(sensorbridgeclient, calibrationresult['sensorSelectionInfo'], calibrationresult['imageType'], KK=calibrationResultUpdate.get('KK'), kc=calibrationResultUpdate.get('kc'), attachedSensorTransform=attachedSensorTransform)
log.info(u'Completed uploading the "%s" calibration result of %s to mujin controller', updateType, calibrationresult['sensorSelectionInfo']) return True
```

```python def ComputePnpTransform(imagePoints, objectPoints, projectionMatrixKK, projectionDistortionKc=None): # type: (np.ndarray, np.ndarray, np.ndarray, np.ndarray) -> Optional[np.ndarray] """ Essentialy a utility function to solve Pnp and return a 4x4 transformation matrix imagePoints: can be 2D or 3D """
validImagePoints = imagePoints[np.where(~np.isnan(imagePoints))[0], :] validObjectPoints = objectPoints[np.where(~np.isnan(imagePoints))[0], :]
if validImagePoints.size == 0: log.error("No valid image points") return None
if not validImagePoints.shape[1] == 2: log.error("Invalid image points shape") return None
if validImagePoints.shape[0] < 4: log.error("Not enough image points. Valid count: %s", validImagePoints.shape[0]) return None
# 2D image if projectionDistortionKc is None: log.warn("Distortion parameters (kc) are None, using zeros instead") projectionDistortionKc = np.zeros(5)
retval, rvec, tvec = cv2.solvePnP( validObjectPoints, validImagePoints, projectionMatrixKK, projectionDistortionKc )
TpattocamFromImage = np.eye(4) TpattocamFromImage[0:3, 0:3] = cv2.Rodrigues(rvec)[0] TpattocamFromImage[0:3, 3] = tvec.flatten()
return TpattocamFromImage
